<TEXT>
an exsheriffs deputy held his former 
girlfriend hostage in a courtroom for nearly seven hours tuesday 
then killed himself and her authorities said 
officials and bystanders heard two muffled shots at 945 pm 
from the courtroom where manny cabano seized juanita hermosilla a 
county clerk who had obtained a restraining order against cabano 
the day before 
paramedics and sheriffs authorities then rushed in and found 
cabano dead with a gunshot wound to the head and ms hermosilla 
critically wounded 
ms hermosilla was taken to john peter smith hospital in fort 
worth where she died at 1017 pm while undergoing emergency 
surgery said eric gordon night administrator both victims were 
in their 40s 
cabano used a 44caliber pistol hed taken to the courtroom in 
the suicidemurder said tarrant county sheriff capt tony wise 
cabano had also seized a 38caliber pistol from the justice of the 
peace in whose courtroom ms hermosilla worked 
the gunman apparently went to ms hermosillas home and opened 
her mail finding court papers relating to the restraining order 
before storming the courtroom sheriffs officials said 
the standoff began when cabano grabbed the woman in justice of 
the peace robert ashmores firstfloor courtroom at the tarrant 
county courthouse at about 3 pm 
police negotiated with cabano sometimes through ms hermosilla 
via telephone during the standoff wise said talks with cabano were 
improving about 8 pm and authorities thought the situation would 
end without bloodshed 
our hopes were building he said 
but then ms hermosilla came on the line and she requested 
that she talk to her boys thats always a bad sign 
wise didnt say whether ms hermosilla was able to speak to her 
children 
police special weapons and tactics units were dispatched to the 
scene but left about 5 pm when the sheriffs department said 
they would take over said fort worth police spokesman doug clarke 
judge ashmore said he worked with the man and knew him the 
sheriff said he worked with him and knew him clarke said 
a sheriffs department dispatcher who did not wish to be 
identified said cabano worked here as a deputy years and years 
ago he then became a bail bondsman until he went bankrupt about a 
year ago 
four of ms hermosillas five children some in their teens 
rushed to the courthouse about 5 pm but were taken away by 
several of her coworkers 
police blocked off the area and evacuated about 300 people in 
the courthouse and the city administration building across the 
street 
</TEXT>
