<DOCNO> AP890802-0038 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
michael harrington remembered as the 
conscience of america who inspired such leaders as the rev 
martin luther king jr and president kennedy with books about 
americas poor has died of cancer at 61 
the political theorist and longtime activist died monday night 
at his home in suburban larchmont the death was announced tuesday 
by the city university of new york where he was a professor of 
political science at queens college 
he wrote 16 books on the problems of massive poverty in the 
midst of affluence and on the cultural stress associated with 
technological advance 
in a 1987 interview with the associated press harrington 
recalled how key individuals including king and kennedy seized 
upon his book the other america poverty in the united states 
to rally for the federal war on poverty 
the luck was that the book came out at a time when there was a 
president of the united states who read books john kennedy and he 
read it harrington said it led him to decide to make poverty 
an issue in the 1964 campaign 
he was killed before he could do it but that set in motion the 
process that led lyndon johnson to declare war on poverty 
harrington also was active in the civil rights movement the 
antiwar movement and the movements against apartheid in south 
africa and against us intervention in central america 
he grew up in st louis in a middleclass family that fared well 
financially even during the great depression 
he became attracted to socialism while at yale law school which 
he attended for a year but harrington did not come facetoface 
with poverty until he went to work as a social worker for the st 
louis board of education a job he got through political pull 
it was a rainy day where i walked into a building and all the 
doors and windows were closed and the building stank so much that 
i almost got nauseous because all of the smells of the backed up 
toilets and the dead rats and the cooking smells of a hundred years 
were all there he recalled in the interview 
at that moment i said to myself this is something i better 
spend the rest of my life trying to abolish 
city university chancellor joseph s murphy said michael 
harringtons intellectual energy dynamism and social commitment 
enriched an entire generation 
he was the conscience of america a champion of the 
downtrodden and afflicted 
harrington was a founder of the democratic socialists of 
america serving as national chairman and cochairman from 1982 
until his death 
he was secretary of the socialist international committee a 
chairman of the socialist party from 1968 to 1972 and of the 
democratic socialist organizing committee from 1973 to 1982 he was 
also a member of the senior seminar of the us department of state 
his latest book socialism past and future was published 
by arcade press last month 
referring to the other america victor navasky editor of 
the nation to which harrington contributed for more than 20 years 
said it was one of the very few times that a book led to a 
federal program the war on poverty 
ever since then theres been a new consciousness that we 
should do something about poor people 
he managed to use the s word and call himself a socialist 
and still have access to the mainstream media and political 
parties 
harrington taught at the universities of paris illinois 
michigan and california at los angeles as well as at harvard 
university and the national war college 
harrington received his bachelors degree from holy cross 
college he received a masters degree from the university of 
chicago in 1949 
he is survived by his wife stephanie gervis harrington and two 
sons private cremation services were held tuesday a memorial is 
planned for september at queens college 
</TEXT>
