<TEXT>
a bus driver lost control of his 
vehicle while he apparently was racing a colleague and it skidded 
off a bridge into a ravine killing 16 people and injuring 35 
others authorities said 
the bus owned by the paper industries corp of the philippines 
was carrying 60 workers to their forest assignments in surigao del 
sur province when the accident occurred according to reports from 
the military and the company 
the bus tore through the railing of the bridge and plunged into 
a ravine according to company spokesman ernie mendoza 
the driver apparently was racing with another company bus that 
was following closely behind mendoza said 
the paper manufacturing company is based in bislig 570 miles 
southeast of the manila capital and 100 miles northeast of davao 
</TEXT>
