<TEXT>
a black priest today announced that he has 
joined suspended black priest rev george a stallings in setting 
up an africanamerican catholic congregation 
stallings who has criticized the catholic church for not 
meeting the needs of its multiethnic congregation said the rev 
bruce greening would assist him as a minister and in forming a 
school at the monthold imani temple 
what is happening at imani temple is in my opinion the right 
method to take said greening who is assigned to the catholic 
diocese of richmond i would like to challenge other black 
priests and other black sisters to do the same 
richmond bishop walter f sullivan issued a statement saying he 
regrets father greenings decision to join imani temple 
by the very fact of his free decision father greening 
automatically disassociates himself from the diocese of richmond 
said sullivan i am relieving him of his duties as principal of 
st marys academy in norfolk effective immediately 
julie sulik spokeswoman of the diocese said sullivan does not 
have the authority to suspend greening from that diocese because he 
is assigned to the society of the divine saviour in milwaukee wis 
greening was working at the norfolk school on a trial basis until 
he decided whether he wanted to remain there sulik said 
milwaukee church officials could not be reached for comment 
stallings said the congregation of the imani temple would be 
meeting aug 19 to discuss the issues they feel should be at the 
forefront of the churchs agenda 
we are going to make sure that when we do deal with those 
issues they are going to be embraced by the people not handed 
down stallings said 
were going to look at teenage pregnancy and the drug 
epidemic in our community he said we see these issues as 
being systematic of greater issues in our society other 
priorities for the black community were unemployment and education 
stallings said 
he also said the imani temple has received several requests from 
other cities to help them establish an africanamerican 
congregation there 
stallings said although he has his eye set on certain cities he 
felt would respond enthusiastically he first wanted to set the 
groundwork for the mother church 
