<TEXT>
austrian conductor herbert von karajan was 
under investigation by the justice department over allegations of 
involvement in nazi persecution but the case against him was 
dropped when he died last month a government lawyer said wednesday 
had he lived there might have been a question of the 
watchlist putting the famed musician on a list of people banned 
from the united states for their nazi pasts said neal m sher who 
heads the justice departments office of special investigations 
among the allegations were that von karajan might have worked 
for the nazi security police and had a role in ridding german 
orchestras of jews and other nonaryans said sher 
the investigation was begun several months ago before von 
karajan died in austria on july 16 at the age of 81 sher said 
we were looking at what his role in nazi persecution might 
have been said sher i dont know where the investigation 
would have led but there might have been a question of the 
watchlist 
thousands of people have been placed on the list including 
austrian president kurt waldheim the office investigated him in 
1986 and reached a finding that played a role in nazi persecution 
during world war ii while he served as an intelligence officer 
von karajan joined the fledgling nazi party in 1933 in austria 
and then rejoined in 1934 when he moved to germany sher said 
under the sponsorship of hermann goering the field marshal who 
founded the gestapo von karajans career flourished 
he was the cultural showpiece of the most horrendous regime 
ever at the time they were throwing people in the ovens he was 
holding concerts sher said 
to say von karajan was just an artist is a revisionist view of 
history sher said 
for two years after the war ended in 1945 von karajan was banned 
from performing by the allied powers who occupied germany because 
of his collaboration with the nazis his first tour of the united 
states in 1954 at the head of the berlin philharmonic which he 
conducted for 34 years was greeted by widespread protests 
von karajan was a frequent visitor to the united states the 
last time in february sher said 
there were many questions about him that deserved answers 
but with his death the case has been closed he said 
