<TEXT>
luiz gonzaga a singer and 
accordion player who almost singlehandedly popularized the lilting 
music of brazils rural northeast died wednesday of pneumonia he 
was 76 
gonzaga suffered from osteoporosis a disease that weakens the 
bones and had been hospitalized for more than a month in recife 
1500 miles northeast of rio hospital officials said by telephone 
gonzaga was born dec 13 1912 in the remote town of exu in the 
heart of the arid sertao or outback 
his father taught him to play the accordion a popular 
instrument in brazils rural northeast and at 12 he was performing 
regularly at local dances in the 1940s he came to rio where 
regional music then was virtually unknown 
at first considered lowbrow gonzaga popularized the baiao 
and forro music with his moon face and trademark leather hat 
typical of northeastern bandits gonzaga became a nationally known 
figure 
his music dealt almost exclusively with the hard life in the 
poor northeast his greatest success was asa branca or white 
wing about a peasant regretfully fleeing the droughtstricken 
backlands but pledging to return when the rains came 
gonzagas body was to be taken back to exu for burial on friday 
