<TEXT>
the house has voted to increase the national 
debt limit temporarily by 70 billion so the treasury wont go into 
default while congress is on its summer recess 
the bill approved 231185 tuesday and sent to the senate adds 
to the debt ceiling of 28 trillion only through oct 31 by then 
congress hopes to complete work on bill boosting the treasurys 
permanent borrowing authority to more than 31 trillion 
the treasury is already bumping up against the 28 trillion 
limit and would be unable to meet its obligations by midaugust 
without additional power to issue debt a us government default 
would be unprecedented 
the house passed the shortterm debt extension after blocking 
228193 an attempt by rep william dannemeyer rcalif to make 
the increase contingent upon house consideration of an amendment to 
the constitution requiring a balanced budget 
the house actually approved the permanent debt increase when it 
passed the fiscal 1990 budget last spring but the legislation has 
been held up in the senate 
several senators plan to use the mustpass legislation to carry 
amendments addressing pet priorities and it could also become the 
vehicle for a new deficitreduction effort by congressional leaders 
and the white house 
the national debt has tripled since the beginning of the decade 
due to the huge budget deficits of the reagan administration the 
treasury has been forced to borrow more and more money to finance 
government spending that exceeds tax receipts 
the annual deficits have gone down from their peak of over 200 
billion a year but nearly 150 billion in red ink will be added to 
the pool this fiscal year 
the grammrudman budget law itself passed as part of a 1985 
debt bill that first put the limit above 2 trillion mandates that 
congress and the president reduce the deficit in fiscal 1990 to 
100 billion 
fiscal 1990 begins oct 1 congress commences its fourweek 
summer recess this saturday 
the shortterm debt limit bill approved by the house on tuesday 
also included a provision requested by the treasury to change the 
way the government accounts for its zerocoupon bonds when 
calculating the debt the change will lessen the immediate impact 
the bonds have on the debt 
 
