people in des moines iowa lead the nation in 
yellow pages usage and new yorkers are the lightest users 
according to a survey released wednesday 
following des moines were tucson ariz little rock ark 
oklahoma city tacoma wash omaha neb albuquerque nm and 
greensboro nc 
the survey was based on more than 60000 telephone interviews 
last year of people in 80 of the nations largest metropolitan 
areas by directory data a division of survey sampling inc of 
fairfield conn 
adults in the des moines area refer to the yellow pages an 
average of 29 times a week while new york adults refer to them an 
average of 087 times a week the survey found 
matt cone a directory data official said he did not want to 
speculate on possible reasons for the differences in usage 
directory data said its survey is the first thorough examination 
of yellow pages usage it is supplying more detailed figures to 
advertisers advertising agencies and publishers 
