the ew scripps co has agreed in principle 
to buy nine cable television systems in the knoxville area and 
eastern tennessee for 100 million the company announced wednesday 
the systems have about 40000 basic subscribers the company 
said 
the systems are a portion of those that intermedia partners 
recently agreed to acquire from jack kent cooke 
through its telescripps subsidiary the company already is the 
largest cable system operator in the knoxville area with the 
additional nine systems scripps will have more than 105000 basic 
subscribers in the area 
we like the greater knoxville area and this is a good 
opportunity to expand our presence there said lawrence a leser 
chairman and chief executive officer of scripps 
